parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Water Leakage into Rear Interior through 5th Door Gap
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water leakage into the rear interior can cause damage to electrical components, carpets, and upholstery, leading to costly repairs and potentially creating a safety hazard.
symptoms: Water accumulation in the rear luggage area
water seepage into the interior through the 5th door gap
difficulty draining water from the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sliding door locking mechanism can cause the door to become stuck in the locked position, trapping occupants inside the vehicle, which can lead to panic, injury, or even fatalities, especially in emergency situations.
symptoms: The sliding door becomes stuck in the locked position
the door cannot be opened manually
the door cannot be opened using the electronic door release
and occupants are unable to exit the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of power and engine stalling can cause a loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: and has no electricity; the engine dies while in motion
including when accelerating or decelerating; the vehicle cannot be restarted immediately; and in some cases
no warning lights or indicators appear on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Low transmission fluid levels can cause the engine to stall or shut off, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine shuts off or dies while in motion
including when accelerating or decelerating; the transmission fluid level is low; and in some cases
no warning lights or indicators appear on the dashboard.
